#!/usr/bin/env perl
use strict;
use warnings;

use version; our $VERSION = qv("v0.1.0");

require App::CPAN::Mini::Visit;
exit App::CPAN::Mini::Visit->run(@ARGV);

__END__

=begin wikidoc

= NAME

visitcpan - run a program against each tarball in a minicpan

= VERSION

This documentation refers to version %%VERSION%%.

= SYNOPSIS

    $ visitcpan OPTIONS

= DESCRIPTION

This program executes code against each distribution in a minicpan repository.
For each distribution tarball, it will:

* unarchive the distribution tarball to a temporary directory 
* change the the temporary directory
* execute user-specified code
* return to the original directory
* clean up the temporary directory

= OPTIONS

 --command|-c       command to executed against each distribution
 --minicpan|-m      directory of a minicpan (defaults to local minicpan 
                    from CPAN::Mini config file)
 --help|-h          this usage info 
 --version|-V       visitcpan program version

= BUGS

Please report any bugs or feature using the CPAN Request Tracker.  
Bugs can be submitted through the web interface at 
[http://rt.cpan.org/Dist/Display.html?Queue=App-CPAN-Mini-Visit]

When submitting a bug or request, please include a test-file or a patch 
to an existing test-file that illustrates the bug or desired feature.

